Calvena. This is the nickname by which Cic. refers to G. Matius, who was bald (calvus). He also calls him Madarra (μαδαρός) and φαλάκρωμα, or ‘bald-head.’ This Matius is the writer of the excellent letter about Caesar which 1 give below (Ep. lxxiii.) He was ever faithful to Caesar, and now was desimus that the assassins of Caesar, who was murdered on March 15 of this year, should be punished. Hence he had incurred the suspicions of Brutus.
